    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I notice that the cjs and esm builds for React InstantSearch (for example) are now bundled, but the original files are still importable as well (to avoid breaking change). This means however that identities between those are not equivalent anymore. If you use `<InstantSearch` from the root import and a widget or connector from its specific file, those will not match. Is there a way in rollup to avoid that? or build with swc directly to get a similar output as babel did before?\r\n\r\nIt should be better now. I used the `preserveModules: true` setting and multiple source entries with Rollup. I also disabled sourcemap generation.",
